# AjayAI — Chat Assistant

🔗 **Live Demo:** [ajaythakur2923.github.io/ai-chat-assistant](https://ajaythakur2923.github.io/ai-chat-assistant)

---

This is a chat assistant I built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It connects to the Groq API which runs Meta's Llama 3.3 model — completely free, no credit card needed, and honestly faster than most paid options I tried.

I wanted to build something that actually works like a real AI chat app, not just a toy project. So I added things like chat history, a typing animation, code formatting, and a proper dark UI. The whole thing runs in the browser with no frameworks or backend needed.

---

## What it does

- Sends your messages to Groq's Llama 3.3 model and shows the response in real time
- Saves your chat history in the browser so it's still there when you come back
- Shows a typing animation while it's waiting for a response
- Formats responses properly — bold text, bullet points, and code blocks with monospace font
- Works on mobile too, with a collapsible sidebar
- Has a few starter prompts on the welcome screen to get going quickly

